The Vice President visited South Carolina and had discussions with young leaders and students about their priorities. They talked about the administration's leadership on the climate crisis and the $370 billion investment in addressing it and creating jobs. They also discussed lowering costs, such as capping the cost of insulin at $35 a month and reducing energy costs. The Vice President highlighted a disconnect between the priorities of everyday Americans and the push to pass a national ban on abortion, emphasizing the importance of addressing everyday needs and respecting a woman's right to make decisions about her own body.